climbs.name: To Bee or Not to Bee

content.description: I've eyed this line for years and finally got on it. After I set up my belay on the arete I poked my head around the corner to scope out the traverse only to hear the buzzing of hundreds of bees only 30' away. Not to be shut down we went for it and the bees kept there distance.  To Bee or Not to Bee starts just right of Intimidation's start on a face crack with an old pin but any other route to get to the shelf half way up the wall will work. Make a belay near the arete on the left then commit to an unprotected traverse around the corner to the left. Pull through the roof and follow the crack that splits the face to the top.
content.location: starts just right of the chimney in the middle of the wall

content.description: Starts in a swallow left facing dihedral on the arete of the huge left facing dihedral in the middle middle of the face. Follow  left arching crack to ledge then pic a line to the top.
Starts in a left facing dihedral past huge jugs out the roof. climb left on the face to a hand crack and take the crack to the top.
Owls Head  sits facing east on the South East Corner of the Mountain range. If you are there odds are no one else is.
